The paper discusses algorithms for near neighbor search, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). The focus on search indexes and data processing also suggests these categories. However, the specific use of approximate proximity graphs and local search metaheuristics may make cs.DS and cs.IR the most likely categories.
